Cells in this table containing 2019–20 data have been randomly adjusted (by perturbation) to avoid the release of confidential data. Discrepancies may occur between sums of the component items and totals. Differences may occur between tables only where estimates are produced for different units (e.g. person, household or expenditure units). See Methodology for more information
(a) Households in the lowest quintile of equivalised disposable household income (incl. imputed rent)
(b) Imputed rent excludes government subsidised housing which is treated as a social transfer in kind
(c) Households in the lowest quintile of equivalised household net worth
(d) Households in the lowest two quintiles of both equivalised disposable household income (incl. imputed rent) and equivalised household net worth

(e) Includes value of public unit trusts, private trusts, debentures and bonds, silent partnerships,  own incorporated business (net of liabilities), own unincorporated business (net of liabilities), other financial investments, and loans to persons not in the same household
(f) Includes value of contents of dwelling, and assets nec
(g) Includes investment loans (excl. business and rental property loans) and loans for other purposes (excl. business and investment loans)
